iConnecting the Base Station to the Magma Access Gateway		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iPick up your CBRS base station and look at the label on the back,		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iwhich should have a serial number like `2112CW5012345`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iIn the core network management interface, go to the left `Equipment`		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
itab, then to the `eNodeB` tab. Click the `Add New` button in the top		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iright to add the base station, and fill in the following:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- In the `Config` tab, `Name` can be filled in arbitrarily.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- In the `Config` tab, fill in `Serial number` with the serial number		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ifrom the base station's label.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
IMagma Add Base Station Interface	/usr/uploads/202504/magma-add-enodeb.png	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- In the `Ran` tab,		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ido not select		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i`eNodeB Managed Externally` (disallow Magma from managing the base		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
istation).		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- In the `Ran` tab, select `Device Class` as `FreedomFi One` (for		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iFreedomFi/Sercomm's indoor base station).		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- In the `Ran` tab, fill in `Cell ID` with `0` (increment by one for		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ieach additional base station).		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- In the `Ran` tab, select `Bandwidth` as 20 MHz for the fastest		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ispeed.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- In the `Ran` tab, fill in `PCI` with `100` (increment by one for		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ieach additional base station).		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- In the `Ran` tab, fill in `TAC` with `1`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- In the `Ran` tab, select `Transmit` as `Enabled` (enable		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
itransmission).		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
