iAlthough we've added the base station to Magma, since the base station		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
idevice defaults to connecting to Helium Mobile's server for		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iconfiguration, it still can't connect to our Access Gateway properly.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iTherefore, we need to hijack the base station's control server		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i`acs.freedomfi.com` to the `eth1` IP address of Magma access gateway		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ivia DNS. Modify your router's DNS settings to hijack the IP of		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i`acs.freedomfi.com` to the `eth1` IP of the machine running the Access		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iGateway. My router uses OpenWRT, so I can add a rule in the Dnsmasq		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iconfiguration page: `/acs.freedomfi.com/192.168.4.2`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iAdditionally, because the port number of the TR-069 server on the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iMagma Access Gateway is different from Helium Mobile's, we need to		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
imodify the port number and some other configurations on the Access		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iGateway.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iOn the Access Gateway, edit `nano /etc/magma/enodebd.yml` and make the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ifollowing changes:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iAfter saving the configuration file, reboot the entire Access Gateway		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
isystem. I found during testing that restarting individual Docker		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
icontainers on the Access Gateway can cause strange issues, such as the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ibase station not being able to connect to the Access Gateway. A full		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ireboot can resolve most strange issues.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iWait a moment, and the core network management interface should show		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ithe status of this base station as `Health` being `Good`. If the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
istatus remains `Bad`, try rebooting the Access Gateway.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
IMagma Base Station Status Interface	/usr/uploads/202504/magma-enodeb-status.png	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iIf you added the indoor base station's serial number to		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i`web_ui_enable_list` to enable the management interface, you can now		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iaccess the base station's management interface via HTTPS, like		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i`https://192.168.1.123/`. The default username and password are		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i`sc_femto` and `tsFid2wz` (from Helium Mobile's Discord:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
hlink	URL:https://discord.com/channels/404106811252408320/836735476659912754/1355330850232995861	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
