iCreating a Data Plan		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iReturn to the core network management interface at		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
hhttps://magma-test.magma.test	URL:https://magma-test.magma.test	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i(or `magma-test.[your own domain]`), go to the left `Traffic` tab,		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ithen to the top `APNs` tab, and click `Create New APN` to create an		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iAPN.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Enter `internet` for `APN ID`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- For `Max Required Bandwidth`, enter `1000000000` (1 Gbps, far		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iexceeding the speed LTE can provide) for both upload and download.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Select `IPV4V6` for `PDN Type`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Keep all other configurations at their defaults.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
IMagma Add APN Interface	/usr/uploads/202504/magma-add-apn.png	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iThen, click the top `Data Plans` tab and click `Create New Data Plan`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- You can enter any value for `Data Plan ID`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Keep both `Download` and `Upload` set to `Unlimited`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
IMagma Add Data Plan Interface	/usr/uploads/202504/magma-add-data-plan.png	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
