iRegistering SIM Cards		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iGo to the left `Subscriber` tab in the management interface, then		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iclick `Manage Subscribers` - `Add Subscribers`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iFor each SIM card you want to add, click the `Add New Row` button in		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ithe top right and enter the SIM card's information:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- In the `IMSI` field, first enter `IMSI`, then the `IMSI15` you used		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iwhen programming the card. For example: `IMSI315010999925470`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- You can enter any value for `Subscriber Name`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Enter the `KI` you used when programming the card in the `Auth Key`		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ifield.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Enter the `OPC` you used when programming the card in the `Auth OPC`		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ifield.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Select `ACTIVE` for `Service` to enable the SIM card.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Select the data plan you created earlier for `Data Plan`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Select the APN you created earlier for `Active APNs`.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Click the checkmark on the right to save.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
